ingredientsDesc: T3 Standards:One vial, 1.0 ml, labeled A, containing 0 ng/dL and six vials, 0.5 mL each, labeled B-G, containing concentrations of approximately 25.0, 50.0, 100.0, 250.0, 500.0 and 1000.0 ng/dL T3 in huamn serum with sodium azide as a preservative.*DSL-3100 (500 Tubes) contains 3 sets of Standards. T3 [I-125] Reagent:One bottle in DSL-3100 (100 Tubes), 22 mL each, containing < 5 μCi (185 kBq) of [I-125]-labeled T3 in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with sodium azide as a preservative.*DSL-3100 (500 Tubes) contains five bottles of reagent. GAMG-Coated Tubes:One hundred (100) plastic tubes with goat anti-mouse gamma globulin immobilized to the inside wall of each tube.*DSL-3100 (500 Tubes) contains 500 tubes.

Anti-T3 Antibody:One vial in DSL-3100 (100 Tubes), 11 mL each, containing anti-T3 mouse monoclonal antibody in a protein-based (BSA) buffer with sodium sodium azide as a preservative.*DSL-3100 (500 Tubes) contains five vials of antibody.T3 Controls:Two vials, 0.5 mL each, Level I and II, containing low and high concentrations of T3 in human serum with sodium azide as a preservative.Wash Concentrate: One bottle, 18 mL in DSL-3100 (100 Tubes), containing a concentrated buffered saline solution with sodium azide as preservative. *DSL-3100 (500 Tubes) contains one 90 mL-bottle of wash concentrate.
